content:
The Expression Engine is an APEX-based formula builder used across multiple areas in OmniStudio, including OmniScripts and Omnistudio Data Mappers. The OmniScript formula builder and attribute rules use a client-side JavaScript expression engine that is evaluated in the browser.

Formula Overview: The formula builder enables you to use functions to define calculations required by your business logic.

To add data to the output of a Data Mapper, define formulas. When you define a formula, map its output to the output JSON or Salesforce object field.

Formulas for insurance rules must return TRUE or FALSE. Use these operators and functions in Omnistudio Data Mappers and Integration Procedures, and in Vlocity Intelligence, eligibility rules, underwriting rules, state rules, and calculation procedures.

You can add custom functions for use in formulas using Apex.
title: Understanding OmniStudio Formulas and Functions
